==English==

===Etymology===
From ''Hispania'' the Latin name for Spain.

===Adjective===
'''Hispanic'''
# [[Spanish]], or of Spanish [[descent]] 
# [[Latin American]], or [[South American]]
#:''Houses in California and Florida exhibit a strong '''Hispanic''' architectural influence.''

===Proper noun===
'''Hispanic'''
# A person of Spanish descent.
#:''There are many famous '''Hispanic''' Americans in the music world.''
# A person from Latin America, or Spain.
# A person residing in the United States, who is of Spanish or Latin American descent. 
#:'''''Hispanics''' are quickly becoming the largest minority in the United States.''

